SIMPLE: edging
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Edging
<hw>Edg"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which
forms an edge or border, as the fringe, trimming, etc., of a garment, or
a border in a garden.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The operation of shaping or dressing the edge of
anything, as of a piece of metal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Edging machine</b></col>, <cd>a machine tool with a
revolving cutter, for dressing edges, as of boards, or metal plates, to
a pattern or templet.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Edgingly</ent>⟦br⟧
